node.title: Victoria records 996 COVID-19 cases and nine deaths
node.alt: A staff member in COVID-19 protective gear putting a nasal swap in a visitors nose.
node.description: There are now 14,260 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 433 people have died during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content: ["Victoria has recorded 996\u00a0new COVID-19 cases and nine\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 14,260\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 433\u00a0people have died during the current Delta outbreak.", "The new cases were detected from 72,010\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There are 357\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 58\u00a0are in intensive care and 35\u00a0are on a ventilator.\u00a0", "The health department said another 65 people were in the ICU, but had been cleared of COVID-19.", "There were 6,692\u00a0doses of vaccine given at state-run centres yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come."]
